      {
        "id": "ee01edacdcdfe3b87be6f2336680e62c9b86d07a",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5072,
          "name": "Patrik Buhr",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "patrik.buhr@est.tech",
          "username": "PatrikBuhr"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-02-26 09:50:30.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThe reactive framework is used internally in this process. But this is not about that. \nThis process fetches events from another process (in a polled fashion). This is done by a REST API that we cannot change in the short perspective \n(it is owned by another component). \nThis solution limits that this process fetches an exessive number of events by only polling when it has capacity.\nThe purpose of the commit is to make a better base for testing high load (and that does not have to mean that it ideal).\n\nAbout testing, it will be done automatically asap. \n\nI can agree that the handling of faults must be done carefully, but it is not only about decreasing a counter. It is also about removing \ntemporary files etc. \n\nWhen it comes about refactoring, there are different future ways forwards. This REST API has inherent problems as I see it (such as there is no \npossibility to limit the number of returned events). There are several ways forwards. But I do not think this is the right \nforum to discuss that. \n\nPlease contact me via mail or skype if you would like to have a more detailed design discussion.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "001bd2f6d16af8ac0ae71984674e7a1cb0f865b5",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2683,
          "name": "Piotr Jaszczyk",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "piotr.jaszczyk@nokia.com",
          "username": "jaszczur"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-02-26 11:17:22.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nOK. I agree that maybe it's not a place and time for that discussion. Change set looks good to me at this stage of development.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
